  "lesson_en": "Be strong and courageous to lead God's people forward",
  "summary_en": "Moses' successor; he led Israel across the Jordan, took Jericho, and conquered Canaan—a model of inheriting the promise by faith and obedience.",
  "witness_en": "God told Joshua four times: be strong and courageous. This shows he was someone who needed encouragement, not a born fearless hero. His courage came from God's word, not his temperament. At the end he said: as for me and my house, we will serve the LORD. A public declaration of personal stand.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, You told Joshua: be strong and courageous, do not be afraid. Say this to me today too. Help me declare openly: as for me and my house, we will serve the LORD. Amen.",
