  "prayer": "主，以利户热情却被你绕过。帮助我的热情不只是多说，而是真正地倾听、真正地同理，说出你真正要说的话。阿们。",
  "typology": {
   "level": "弱预表",
   "strength": "weak_devotional",
   "summary": "年轻发言者强调神的公义与教育性苦难；有中保解释者的影子但不完整。",
   "scriptures": [
    "伯32-37"
   ],
   "motifs": []
  },
  "lesson_en": "Young passion and limited insight",
  "summary_en": "A young man who appeared after Job's three friends, angry that the three elders could not answer Job, who defended God with many words, and was finally passed over by God without comment.",
  "witness_en": "He waited long before speaking, deferring to elders because of his youth. His starting point was zeal for God—he sincerely wanted to defend God. But his words were many, and in the end God mentioned only Job and the three friends, not him. Zeal without humility, many words yet off the mark. Young zeal needs time and suffering to mature.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Elihu was passionate yet was passed over by You. Help my passion not be merely speaking much, but truly listening, truly empathizing, and saying what You truly want said. Amen.",
