  "witness_en": "He and his brother John were once called 'sons of thunder,' and once asked Jesus to let them sit in high positions. But in the end he became the first apostle to shed blood for the faith. From a son of thunder to a martyr—this is the deepest fulfillment of discipleship. God sometimes seals faith with a life, and his death did not make the church retreat, but made believers braver.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, James son of Zebedee was the first apostle martyred for You. Help me have such faithfulness—not impulsive emotion, but real commitment, willing to pay the cost for You. Amen.",
