  "prayer": "主，你看见拿但业在无花果树底下。你也看见我一切隐藏的地方。帮助我像他一样，被完全知道，仍然完全信任你。阿们。",
  "lesson_en": "A true Israelite with no deceit",
  "summary_en": "That is, Nathanael, whom Jesus praised as 'a true Israelite, in whom there is no deceit.' At first he doubted whether anything good could come from Nazareth, but after Philip persuaded him to come, he at once recognized Jesus as the Son of God.",
  "witness_en": "Jesus saw him coming and said: behold, a true Israelite, in whom there is no deceit. Nathanael asked: how do You know me? Jesus said, I saw you under the fig tree. That one sentence was enough. A heart without deceit is worthy of God's complete knowing. He was fully known, and therefore fully trusted.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, You saw Nathanael under the fig tree. You also see all my hidden places. Help me, like him, to be fully known and still fully trust You. Amen.",
