  "prayer": "主，达太问出了我们很多人心里的问题。帮助我有勇气在你面前问真实的疑惑，然后安静听你的回答。阿们。",
  "lesson_en": "The faithfulness of an unknown apostle",
  "summary_en": "Also called Judas (not Iscariot), who at the Last Supper asked Jesus: Lord, why will You reveal Yourself to us and not to the world?—voicing the doubt in many believers' hearts.",
  "witness_en": "He appears only in the apostle list and one question. But that question is no small one: why reveal Yourself only to us? Jesus' answer was: whoever loves Me, My Father will love him, and We will come to him and make Our home with him. Thaddaeus represents every unknown, unrecorded disciple who truly followed. God's kingdom needs not only Peter and Paul, but also Thaddaeus.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Thaddaeus asked the question many of us hold in our hearts. Help me have courage to ask my true doubts before You, then quietly listen to Your answer. Amen.",
