  "applications": [
   "你是否有勇气在别人庆祝胜利时，说出神要求的仁慈？",
   "俄底的信息不是审判，而是提醒——这种温柔的先知话语同样需要勇气"
  ],
  "scriptures": [
   "代下28:9",
   "代下28:11",
   "代下28:15"
  ],
  "prayer": "主，俄底一人阻止了二十万人的苦难。帮助我在有机会阻止伤害的时候，有俄底的勇气站出来说话，相信你的话能软化人心。阿们。",
  "lesson_en": "A prophet's word can also stop the cruelty of the victorious",
  "summary_en": "A prophet of Samaria who, when the northern kingdom greatly defeated the south and seized two hundred thousand captives, stepped out alone to stop it, demanding the captives be released; the leaders obeyed, and the captives were properly returned—one of Scripture's most moving humanitarian moments.",
  "witness_en": "He went out to meet the triumphant army and said: you have won, but God does not want you to destroy your brothers. One man, no army, no political standing, only God's word—and four leaders obeyed him, releasing all the captives. Sometimes God's word can change people's hearts in an instant.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Oded alone stopped the suffering of two hundred thousand. Help me, when I have a chance to stop harm, have Oded's courage to step out and speak, trusting Your word can soften hearts. Amen.",
  "follow_en": [
   "At Israel's proudest moment of great victory and capturing 200,000 southern compatriots, stepping out alone to stop them: 'the LORD's anger is against you' (2 Chr 28:9-11)",
   "Caring for the captives' humanitarian plight, bringing about their being given food and clothing and escorted home—one of the OT's most moving humanitarian moments"
  ],
  "caution_en": [],
