  "prayer": "主，罗得的妻子一回头就失去了一切。帮助我在你说不要回头的地方，有彻底告别旧生活的勇气，不只是身体离开，更是心完全转向前方。阿们。",
  "lesson_en": "Looking back is the most fatal disobedience to God's command",
  "summary_en": "Fleeing Sodom, she was clearly commanded by the angels not to look back, yet looked back during the escape and at once became a pillar of salt. Jesus Himself cited her as a warning: remember Lot's wife.",
  "witness_en": "There was only one command: do not look back. She looked back. Scripture does not explain why—nostalgia? curiosity? reluctance? Whatever it was, that one look back ended everything. God's command needs no reason, only obedience. Jesus said: remember Lot's wife—these words span thousands of years, still asking us: where is your heart?",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Lot's wife lost everything the moment she looked back. Help me, where You say do not look back, have courage to bid a thorough farewell to the old life—not only leaving physically, but turning my heart fully forward. Amen.",
