  "prayer": "主，保护我不要成为亚希多弗——智慧卓绝却以自我为中心。帮助我的才能和判断始终向你的旨意俯伏，而不是凌驾于你之上。阿们。",
  "lesson_en": "Wisdom not centered on God must finally self-destruct",
  "summary_en": "David's most trusted counselor, called 'like inquiring of the word of God,' yet who betrayed David during Absalom's rebellion, and after his counsel was defeated by Hushai, hanged himself—a tragedy of talent and loyalty collapsing together.",
  "witness_en": "His counsel was so precise that Scripture says 'when one inquired of him, it was as inquiring of the word of God.' But his wisdom was not rooted in God, but in his own status and judgment. When his counsel was rejected, he realized defeat was certain, went home to put his affairs in order, and hanged himself—the wisdom of despair, not of hope.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, protect me from becoming Ahithophel—brilliant in wisdom yet self-centered. Help my talent and judgment always bow to Your will, rather than rise above You. Amen.",
  "follow_en": [],
