  "summary_en": "A woman believer of the Philippian church who had labored with Paul for the gospel, yet had a dispute with her co-worker Syntyche; Paul named them in his letter, asking them to reconcile in the Lord—one of church history's most famous cases of co-worker conflict.",
  "witness_en": "Paul did not avoid this conflict, but named them in a public letter and urged reconciliation. To be named by Paul as one who 'labored with me for the gospel' shows she truly served; but the dispute became a stumbling block to the witness. Discord among co-workers is no small matter; it can make the world misunderstand the gospel.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, protect my relationships with co-workers, that I may be reconciled in Christ, and let our unity be a witness to the gospel. Amen.",
