  "lesson_en": "Humility after pride is the true knowledge of God",
  "summary_en": "King of Babylon who personally witnessed Daniel's three friends saved from the fire and Daniel interpreting dreams, yet was proud and arrogant, struck by God to live like a beast for seven years, finally humbly acknowledging the Most High God's sovereignty—the most dramatic case of repentance among Gentile kings.",
  "witness_en": "After seven years, he lifted his eyes to heaven, and his reason returned—he said: I bless the Most High and honor the One who lives forever. This is the truest theology spoken by a Gentile king. Pride at its extreme, and God used seven years of wilderness to bring him back. No one is too proud for God to deal with.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Nebuchadnezzar traded seven years for truly knowing You. Help me not wait until I'm beaten into the wilderness to be humble, but acknowledge before You today: all glory is Yours. Amen.",
