  "scriptures": [],
  "prayer": "主啊，伊格那丢在赴死途中仍写信坚固众教会。求你给我这样的心——在自己的患难里仍顾念别人，把苦难化为牧养与祝福，至死持守你真实的神人二性。阿们。",
  "lesson_en": "Willingly ground for the faith",
  "summary_en": "Bishop of the church in Antioch, escorted to Rome for execution (devoured by beasts). Along the way he wrote seven letters to various churches, emphasizing Christ's true divine-human natures, church unity, and the joy of martyrdom, calling himself 'the wheat of Christ, willing to be ground by the beasts into pure bread.'",
  "witness_en": "He regarded martyrdom as the highest honor of union with Christ, strengthening the churches by letters even unto death, turning suffering into shepherding.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Ignatius wrote to strengthen the churches even on his way to death. Give me such a heart—to care for others even in my own affliction, turning suffering into shepherding and blessing, holding fast to Your true divine-human natures unto death. Amen.",
