  "lesson_en": "Serving with reason, martyred for the true faith",
  "summary_en": "Originally a philosopher seeking truth, who after coming to the Lord wore a philosopher's robe and preached everywhere, writing the Apologies and the Dialogue with Trypho—the first-generation Christian apologist, who defended the faith before the Roman emperor and was finally martyred.",
