  "scriptures": [],
  "prayer": "主啊，沃姆布兰德在地牢酷刑中经历你的同在，出来后为逼迫者祷告、为受苦肢体发声。求你坚固今天受逼迫的教会，也给我与他们一同受苦、为他们代求的心，叫我的安逸不使我冷漠。阿们。",
  "lesson_en": "Not forsaking faith in prison, speaking for the suffering after release",
  "summary_en": "A Romanian pastor imprisoned fourteen years under the communist regime, who endured torture yet did not abandon his faith, and prayed for his persecutors. After release he founded 'The Voice of the Martyrs,' wrote 'Tortured for Christ,' exposing to the world and serving the persecuted body of Christ.",
  "witness_en": "In the dungeon he experienced the Lord's presence; coming out, he held no grudge, but devoted the rest of his life to speaking for the suffering body.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Wurmbrand experienced Your presence in dungeon torture, and after release prayed for his persecutors and spoke for the suffering body. Strengthen the persecuted church today, and give me a heart to suffer with them and intercede for them, that my comfort may not make me cold. Amen.",
