  "prayer": "主啊，弗拉维教我默想你隐秘的护理，在丧亲与逼迫中仍以你为安慰。求你开我的眼，叫我看见你在我一生大小事上慈爱智慧的编织；当我不明白时，仍安息在你美善的护理中。阿们。",
  "lesson_en": "Meditating on and trusting God's hidden providence",
  "summary_en": "A Puritan pastor in Dartmouth, England, ejected for nonconformity, who still risked secretly preaching and shepherding fishermen and common folk by the seaside and in the woods. His classic 'The Mystery of Providence' teaches people to meditate on, remember, and trust God's hidden arrangement in all of life's matters; and he wrote 'Keeping the Heart' on watching the inner self. Through bereavement and persecution, he found comfort in God's providence.",
  "witness_en": "He taught people to 'look back and count the footsteps of God's providence'—life's seemingly random, scattered events are all finely woven together by a wise and loving God. Seeing this, one finds rest in affliction.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Flavel taught me to meditate on Your hidden providence, finding comfort in You through bereavement and persecution. Open my eyes to see Your loving, wise weaving in all of life's matters; when I don't understand, let me still rest in Your good providence. Amen.",
