  "scriptures": [],
  "prayer": "主啊，布雷纳德体弱多病、一生短暂，却以恒切的祷告与舍己服事，影响了世代。求你叫我不轻看自己的软弱与有限，乃以为失丧者切切代求、甘心舍己的心服事你，把果效交在你手中。阿们。",
  "lesson_en": "A short, weak life of far-reaching influence",
  "summary_en": "A young man in early America who did missions among the North American Indians. His life was short (he died of tuberculosis at 29), frail and often in spiritual low points, yet through persistent prayer, intercession, and self-denial he served the natives and saw revival. Edwards compiled and published his diary, and 'The Life and Diary of David Brainerd' became one of history's most influential spiritual biographies, inspiring countless later missionaries like William Carey and Hudson Taylor.",
  "witness_en": "His short, weak, seemingly unsuccessful life had influence lasting centuries—proving what God values most is not strength and achievement, but a heart that prays earnestly for the lost and willingly denies itself.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Brainerd, frail and short-lived, served by persistent prayer and self-denial, influencing the generations. Make me not despise my weakness and limits, but serve You with a heart of earnest intercession for the lost and willing self-denial, leaving the fruit in Your hands. Amen.",
