  "lesson_en": "Deep cultural identification, boldly entering an unreached people",
  "summary_en": "An American missionary who at nineteen, alone and without mission support, entered the dangerous Motilone tribe on the Colombia-Venezuela border. He did not impose Western culture, but patiently learned their language, blended into their life, and shared the gospel in ways they could understand, bringing the whole tribe's conversion and transformation, and introducing medicine and education, accepted by the tribe as one of their own. Held hostage by guerrillas for years, he still did not give up.",
