  "lesson_en": "Holding the rope at the rear for front-line missions",
  "summary_en": "An English Baptist theologian and pastor, William Carey's most important supporter. He rekindled the mission of 'preach the gospel to all' with theology (refuting the inactive 'hyper-Calvinism' that didn't evangelize), and with Carey and others co-founded the Baptist Missionary Society (BMS), personally raising funds, mobilizing, and organizing at home in England, providing ongoing rear support for front-line missionaries. Carey once said: 'I will go down into the [Indian] mine, but you must hold the rope.' Fuller was the one 'holding the rope.'",
