  "lesson_en": "The branch that inherited the blessing",
  "summary_en": "Noah's son, blessed with Japheth for honoring his father. Noah blessed, 'Blessed be the LORD, the God of Shem,' and the godly line was carried by Shem, from whom Abraham came.",
  "witness_en": "Shem was Noah's eldest son. After Noah's drunkenness, he and Japheth went in backward to cover their father's nakedness, not looking at his shame; so Noah blessed Shem, saying 'Blessed be the LORD, the God of Shem.' This branch was later linked to Abraham and to the genealogy of salvation.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Shem covered his father's shame with respect and inherited the blessing. Make me cover others' weakness with respect and love, treasuring and passing on the blessing You give. Amen.",
