  "lesson_en": "God breaks through amid chaos, preserving the line of salvation",
  "summary_en": "Son of Judah and Tamar, who at birth 'broke through' first, hence named Perez ('breakthrough'). The genealogies in Ruth and Matthew both record him as an ancestor of David and Christ.",
  "witness_en": "Perez's birth was itself a sign: in the twins' contest he broke through first, his name a commentary on his life. He came from a relationship people saw as shameful, yet was chosen by God to carry the line of promise of Judah's tribe—Boaz, David, down to Christ all came from him. The elders of Bethlehem once blessed Boaz's house to be 'like the house of Perez.' God's plan of salvation is never blocked by human sin and chaos; He will open a breakthrough for His own promise.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, You are the breakthrough Lord from Perez's line. Sin and death once locked humanity in despair, yet You broke through from the grave, opening a new and living way for us. Break through the deadlocks in my life too, that Your promise may flow unhindered in me. Amen.",
