  "witness_en": "Oholiab lived almost his whole life behind Bezalel's name, yet Scripture solemnly records: God Himself appointed him to 'work with Bezalel.' He did not vie for first place, but devoted the skill God gave fully to building the tabernacle, and taught his skill to others. God's dwelling is never built by one genius alone, but by a Spirit-equipped community of one heart. In the kingdom, those willingly playing supporting roles share God's remembrance with those who lead.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, You build the church as God's dwelling, and call me to share in it. Give me Oholiab's heart: not vying for position, willingly behind others, using the gift You gave to be built together with all the members into a place where God dwells by the Spirit. Amen.",
