  "lesson_en": "Prophesying with the mouth, coveting unjust gain in the heart, finally cast away",
  "summary_en": "A Gentile seer hired with rich reward by Balak king of Moab to curse Israel, who, stopped by God, instead spoke blessing and prophesied 'a star shall come out of Jacob.' Yet he later devised a scheme to lead Israel into immorality and idolatry, and was finally killed. The New Testament cites him three times as a warning.",
  "witness_en": "Balaam is one of the most sobering figures in Scripture: he knew the true God, could receive true revelation, even spoke a prophecy pointing to the Messiah—'a star shall come out of Jacob, a scepter shall rise out of Israel.' Yet his heart loved the wages of unrighteousness; knowing God forbade it he tempted Him again and again, and finally by trickery made God's people stumble. Gift is not life, and the pulpit is not heaven. Even his donkey saw the angel blocking the way, but his eyes were blinded by money.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, keep my heart far from Balaam's way: not coveting unjust gain, not treating gifts as a business, not gambling after You have said 'no.' You are the bright morning star out of Jacob; may I look only to You, fear You, and serve You to the end with a pure heart. Amen.",
