  "lesson_en": "A foolish, hard, ungrateful heart makes one miss grace and bring ruin on oneself",
  "summary_en": "A great rich man of Maon, his name meaning 'fool,' hard and harsh in nature. David's men had protected his shepherds and flocks, yet on the joyful sheep-shearing day he insulted David and refused to repay. Ten days later the LORD struck him, and he died.",
  "witness_en": "Nabal has no witness of trusting God; he is a living picture of 'the fool says in his heart there is no God.' Rich in estate yet hard as stone, shown the grace of protection yet returning insult, with disaster looming he was still feasting and drunk in revelry. His wife Abigail said it plainly: 'His name is Nabal, and folly is with him.' God Himself executed judgment, a warning to all who despise grace.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, save me from Nabal's folly: that hardness amid wealth, that ingratitude after grace, that numbness in revelry. You are the generous and gracious Lord; put Your wisdom and mercy in my heart, that I be one who, shown grace, also shows grace. Amen.",
