  "summary_en": "A man of Gath. After the Uzzah incident, David dared not bring the ark into the city of David, so it was sent to the house of Obed-Edom. The ark stayed in his house three months, and the LORD blessed him and all his household, and this blessing became the occasion for David to bring the ark up again.",
  "witness_en": "When everyone feared the ark because of Uzzah's death, Obed-Edom opened his door to the sign of God's presence. What others saw as 'danger' became overflowing blessing in a household of reverent obedience—'the LORD blessed Obed-Edom and all his household.' He witnesses a simple yet profound truth: God's presence is not a threat to flee, but a blessing to welcome; and this blessing finally came in Immanuel Christ to all who receive Him.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, You are Immanuel, God with us. Enter my home, as the ark stayed at Obed-Edom's house, that my whole household may be blessed by Your presence. May my home be ever open to You, a place You delight to dwell. Amen.",
