  "lesson_en": "Faithfully proclaiming God's word: daring to expose sin and to declare the covenant of grace",
  "summary_en": "A prophet of David's reign. He proclaimed to David God's eternal covenant—that David's offspring and throne would be established forever; and after David's sin he rebuked the king to his face with the parable of the ewe lamb: 'You are the man!' leading David to repentance.",
  "witness_en": "Nathan's witness is double-edged faithfulness: on one hand proclaiming the greatest grace—the Davidic covenant pointing to the Messiah; on the other facing the greatest sin—kingship however great is not above God's justice. He neither flattered for favor nor shrank back from the king's wrath, using a wise parable to make a hard heart hear God's voice. Behind David's psalm of repentance (Psalm 51) stands this faithful messenger.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, You are the prophet greater than Nathan, who personally exposes my sin and personally fulfilled the Davidic covenant. Give me faithfulness and courage, not to be silent when I should speak, nor to mix in my own bias when conveying Your word. Amen.",
