  "summary_en": "Hiram was a skilled craftsman of Tyre, expert in bronzework and various crafts, invited by Solomon to share in building the temple. He made the temple's bronze pillars, the bronze sea, and various vessels, offering his skill to God's dwelling.",
  "witness_en": "Though of Gentile background, Hiram fully offered the wisdom and skill God gave, using it to build the house of the LORD. His witness reminds us: skill and profession are not worldly private property, but vessels that can be offered to God to build His dwelling. When one willingly uses gifts on God's project, even ordinary craft becomes holy work glorifying God.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, thank You for the various gifts and skills You give. Help me, like Hiram, offer up the work of my hands, sharing in building Your spiritual temple. May all I do be for the glory of Your name. Amen.",
