  "typology": {
   "level": "中等预表",
   "strength": "narrative_pattern",
   "summary": "同沙得拉，不拜金像被丢火窑，蒙神同在。",
   "scriptures": [
    "但3"
   ],
   "motifs": [
    "suffering_righteous"
   ]
  },
  "lesson_en": "Bound into the fire yet set free in the fire",
  "summary_en": "Abednego was one of Daniel's three friends, who with Shadrach and Meshach refused to bow to the golden image and was thrown bound into the blazing furnace. The ropes binding them were burned off, the three walked in the fire with the fourth figure like a son of the gods, and came out unharmed.",
  "witness_en": "Abednego was thrown bound into the furnace, but the fire only burned off the ropes binding him. The world thought the furnace was the end, but God made it the start of walking with the Lord and being promoted by the king's order. His experience witnesses: people can bind God's servant, but cannot block God's presence; what persecution burns is often only our bonds.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, thank You for walking with Your servants in the blazing fire, burning off the bonds yet preserving life. Make me experience the mystery of this presence in trial, coming out of the furnace with Your praise on my lips. Amen.",
