  "lesson_en": "God rules the hearts of kings to accomplish the restoration of His temple",
  "summary_en": "Darius was a Persian king who, when the temple rebuilding was questioned, ordered a search of the archives, found Cyrus' decree, confirmed and funded the rebuilding command, forbade anyone to hinder it, and the temple was completed.",
  "witness_en": "When enemies tried to use the government to stop the temple work, Darius' search and decree became the very safeguard of God's work—not only permitting the rebuilding, but supplying the cost from the king's treasury. He witnesses Proverbs' word that the king's heart is in the LORD's hand: God can turn even Gentile power to serve the restoration of His dwelling, and no power can truly hinder His work.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, the hearts of kings are in Your hand. Thank You for preserving the temple's completion through Darius' decree. Rule today's authorities too, that the building of Your church go unhindered and Your name be glorified. Amen.",
