  "summary_en": "Artaxerxes was a Persian king who first permitted Ezra to bring the law back to teach the people, then sent the cupbearer Nehemiah back to Jerusalem to rebuild the wall, granting a decree and materials, becoming a key driver of the return and rebuilding.",
  "witness_en": "Ezra said: blessed be the LORD, the God of our fathers, who put such a thing as this into the king's heart, to beautify the house of the LORD in Jerusalem. Nehemiah found favor before the king because the good hand of God was on him. Artaxerxes' decree witnesses: the pen of history is in God's hand, and even an empire's administrative orders serve the restoration of God's city and law.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, You moved Artaxerxes to grant the rebuilding of Your city. Move the hearts of those in power today too, paving the way for the gospel and the building of the church; may the authority of all nations be under Your feet. Amen.",
