  "summary_en": "Eliashib was the high priest in Nehemiah's time, who had taken part in building the Sheep Gate, yet became allied by marriage with the enemy Tobiah, even preparing for him a large room in the temple courts to store furniture. When Nehemiah returned he threw out all Tobiah's furniture and cleansed the room.",
  "witness_en": "Eliashib's failure is a heavy warning bell: as high priest he should have guarded the temple's holiness, yet for personal ties and in-law relations he welcomed God's enemy into God's courts. When holy office allies with worldly power, God's house is breached first from within. He stands in contrast to Christ—the High Priest who cleansed the temple, without defilement.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, You cleansed the temple, and would cleanse this temple that is me. Shine on the corners in me secretly allied with the world, throw out all the defiling 'furniture,' that my service may be holy and without blemish. Amen.",
