  "lesson_en": "The culture of repaying violence with violence is finally replaced by Christ's kingdom of forgiveness",
  "summary_en": "Lamech was a descendant of Cain, the first polygamist recorded in Scripture. He boasted to his two wives of killing a man in revenge, declaring 'if Cain is avenged sevenfold, then Lamech seventy-sevenfold,' treating violence and revenge as glory.",
  "witness_en": "Lamech has no witness of trusting God; he is an amplification of Cain's way: Cain still feared after killing, but Lamech made a song to boast after killing. His 'seventy-sevenfold revenge' sharply contrasts with Jesus' teaching Peter to forgive 'seventy times seven,' showing that only Christ can stop humanity's cycle of blood for blood.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, Lamech boasted of revenge, but You on the cross said 'Father, forgive them.' Save me from the nature of an eye for an eye, put Your seventy-times-seven forgiveness in my heart, that I be a child of peace in a violent age. Amen.",
  "follow_en": [],
