  "lesson_en": "An empire that makes a name for itself must fall; only Christ's kingdom endures forever",
  "summary_en": "Nimrod was a descendant of Ham through Cush, 'the first mighty one on earth,' 'a mighty hunter before the LORD.' He built the earliest human empire, his kingdom beginning with Babel and other cities, linked to the system of self-glory the Tower of Babel represents.",
  "witness_en": "Nimrod has no witness of trusting God; he represents humanity's first concentrated wave of power and ambition after the flood: founding a kingdom by force, making a name by building. Babel's slogan 'let us make a name for ourselves, lest we be scattered' is the spirit of this system. God confused their language to stop it, witnessing that every work exalting self cannot stand before God.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, Nimrod made a name and built a kingdom for himself, but You emptied Yourself and took the form of a servant. Save me from the ambition of spreading my own name; let what I build all my life be not a Babel but Your kingdom, that Your name be hallowed. Amen.",
