  "witness_en": "Ishmael himself was also heard by God (his name means 'God hears'); in the wilderness when dying God opened Hagar's eyes to see a well. But in salvation history he represents the result of using fleshly methods to 'help' God fulfill the promise: not only failing to accomplish it but bringing lasting tension in the home. His existence witnesses that the son of promise must come from God's power, not human flesh.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, You are the true offspring of God's promise, yet I often try to accomplish spiritual things by the flesh. Forgive my impatience and self-will, teach me to wait quietly for the Father's time, that I be a free child born by promise, no longer under the yoke of slavery. Amen.",
