  "lesson_en": "The office of mediator is established by God; one must not seize it",
  "summary_en": "Korah was a descendant of Levi through Kohath, already serving at the tabernacle, yet joined Dathan, Abiram, and 250 leaders to attack Moses and Aaron, seeking the priesthood for himself. The earth opened and swallowed the rebels, fire consumed the 250 who offered incense, and God thus made clear His chosen mediator.",
  "witness_en": "Korah has no witness of faith, only a warning of usurpation: under the banner of 'all the congregation are holy,' he was in fact discontent with God's arrangement and coveted a higher office. Jude lists him with Cain and Balaam on the way of destruction. Notably, Korah's descendants did not perish, but later wrote several psalms of the sons of Korah, witnessing God's mercy surpassing the fathers' rebellion.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, You are the one Mediator God established, yet I often covet position in my heart and resent my place. Tear down Korah's ambition in me, give me a heart content to be lowly, that I may be faithful to the end in the place You measured to me. Amen.",
