  "lesson_en": "Rather give up life than sell the inheritance God gave",
  "summary_en": "Naboth was a Jezreelite who owned a vineyard right beside King Ahab's palace. Ahab wanted to buy it with money or a trade, but Naboth refused because it was the inheritance the LORD gave his fathers. Jezebel then framed him with false witnesses of blaspheming God and king, and Naboth was stoned to death; God through Elijah declared judgment on Ahab's house.",
  "witness_en": "Naboth's witness lies in loyalty to God's law: by the law, the inheritance was apportioned by God and not to be sold permanently (Lev 25:23). Facing royal power and gain, he chose to fear God over the king, and was framed by false witness and unjustly killed outside the city. God was not silent—Elijah was at once sent to pronounce judgment, and dogs licked Ahab's blood where Naboth's blood had flowed. God remembers the blood of the innocent.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, Naboth was killed by false witness for holding the inheritance God gave; You even more were condemned and crucified outside the city by false witness for our sake. Give me a loyal heart, rather to suffer loss than sell what You entrust; in injustice give me quietness, trusting You are the avenging Lord. Amen.",
