  "prayer": "主啊，亚那披着圣职却怀私心，暗中不义审判祢的爱子。求祢洁净我事奉的动机，使我不以属灵身份谋私利，乃在隐密处持守公义。阿们。",
  "lesson_en": "Self-interest cloaked in holy office is most dangerous",
  "summary_en": "A former high priest, Caiaphas' father-in-law, who though retired still held the power of the priestly family, and privately tried Jesus at night.",
  "witness_en": "Annas was the true power-holder of the priestly clique of that day—five of his sons and his son-in-law Caiaphas served as high priest in succession, and the temple trade's interests were deeply entangled. When Jesus was arrested, He was first brought before Annas for a private trial, which itself was illegal. He wore the most sacred office, yet within was maintaining the family's power and vested interests. Annas reminds us: the most dangerous corruption is not open evil, but self-interest and scheming wrapped in holy office, in a religious cloak.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Annas wore holy office yet harbored self-interest, secretly trying Your beloved Son unjustly. Cleanse my motives in service, that I not use a spiritual identity for private gain, but hold justice in secret. Amen.",
