  "lesson_en": "Staying home, yet the heart can be far from the father",
  "summary_en": "The elder son in the parable who, though law-abiding, was angry at the father throwing a feast for his returned brother and refused to go in.",
  "witness_en": "The elder son never left home, labored for years, and never disobeyed his father's command. Yet when his brother returned and the father held a feast, he 'was angry and refused to go in.' He said to his father: I have served you these many years, and you never gave me a young goat... 'but when this son of yours came,' you killed the fattened calf for him! He kept the rules, but his heart was full of comparison, self-righteousness, and bitterness—at home, but his heart far from the father's heart. The father came out and pleaded: 'You are always with me, and all that is mine is yours.' The elder son warns us: the law-abiding too can be unable, through self-righteousness, to share the father's joy.",
  "prayer_en": "Heavenly Father, the prodigal's elder brother stayed home, yet his heart was far from You through self-righteousness. Heal the comparison and bitterness in me, that I rejoice over others being shown grace and truly enjoy the blessing of being with You. Amen.",
