  "prayer": "主耶稣，十字架上的强盗最后一刻转向祢，就蒙应许同进乐园。谢谢祢的恩典如此浩大；求祢使我单单信靠祢的怜悯，也把这盼望带给绝境中的人。阿们。",
  "lesson_en": "Last-moment faith is also remembered by the Lord",
  "summary_en": "One of the robbers crucified with Jesus, who in his final hour repented, asked the Lord to remember him, and was promised that very day to enter paradise together.",
  "witness_en": "Both robbers were crucified with Jesus. One mocked, but the other, in the last few hours of life, saw the truth: he rebuked his companion, 'Do you not fear God, since you are under the same sentence?' admitting he was 'justly' punished, and recognizing the innocent dying Jesus as King: 'Jesus, remember me when You come into Your kingdom!' He had not been baptized, done no good works, had no time to make amends—only a faith turning to Christ. The Lord at once promised: 'Today you will be with Me in paradise.' He is the purest witness of grace: salvation by grace through faith, unrelated to merit—even at the last moment.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord Jesus, the robber on the cross turned to You at the last moment and was promised entry into paradise. Thank You that Your grace is so great; make me trust only Your mercy, and bring this hope to the desperate. Amen.",
