  "prayer": "主啊，方伯士求保罗以通达的心渴慕祢的道，纵有拦阻仍信了主。求祢赐我谦卑寻道的心，不因学识地位自满，并为一切真心寻求祢的人除去拦阻。阿们。",
  "lesson_en": "A man of understanding hungers for the truth",
  "summary_en": "The proconsul of Cyprus, a man of understanding, who hungered to hear God's word; when the magician Elymas opposed, Paul rebuked him to blindness, and the proconsul believed.",
  "witness_en": "Sergius Paulus was a Roman-appointed proconsul—a man of position and discernment, 'a man of understanding.' He actively sent for Barnabas and Saul, 'wanting to hear the word of God.' The magician Elymas (Bar-Jesus) beside him strongly opposed, to turn the proconsul from the faith. Paul, filled with the Spirit, fixed his eyes and rebuked this 'son of the devil,' striking him temporarily blind. The proconsul, seeing what happened, was 'astonished at the teaching of the Lord' and believed. Sergius Paulus reminds us: those with position and learning also need, and can, hunger for truth; and for the one who truly seeks, God will clear away the hindrance.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, the proconsul Sergius Paulus hungered for Your word with an understanding heart, and believed despite hindrance. Give me a humble, seeking heart, not self-satisfied in learning and status, and clear away hindrances for all who truly seek You. Amen.",
