  "witness_en": "The chief baker was imprisoned with the cupbearer, and Joseph interpreted his dream too, but it was an omen of doom: in three days he would be hanged on a tree. After three days it came true. In the same prison, both having dreams interpreted, the ends were poles apart—God's word is true, judgment and rescue each by its reality.",
