  "witness_en": "Eliphaz the Temanite was the foremost of Job's three friends, urging Job to confess his sin by the traditional wisdom 'good rewarded with good, evil with evil.' His words were not without reason, but applied in the wrong place—Job in his suffering was not being punished for sin. God later rebuked them: 'you have not spoken of Me what is right, as My servant Job has.'",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Eliphaz judged Job's suffering with right doctrine. Make me, when accompanying the suffering, first have compassion and be careful in judging, lest I wound people with truth. Amen.",
  "follow_en": [
   "Having the initial intent to comfort the suffering (the first seven days of silent companionship)"
  ],
  "caution_en": [
   "Judging another's suffering by a rigid cause-and-effect",
   "Right doctrine with wrong application"
  ],
  "applications_en": [
   "When accompanying the suffering, listen first rather than rush to judge",
   "Don't condemn the suffering with 'you must have sinned to suffer'",
   "Be careful: even right doctrine can be applied to the wrong person"
  ]
