  "witness_en": "Zelophehad was a man of the tribe of Manasseh who died in the wilderness with no sons, only five daughters. Though sonless, his daughters argued their case and obtained the inheritance, and through this God set a statute that daughters could inherit. A man 'without heirs' became the occasion for a just statute.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, though Zelophehad had no son, through his daughters You set a just statute. Make me still trust You amid lack, knowing You can bring blessing out of insufficiency. Amen.",
