  "witness_en": "Barzillai was an old man of Gilead, exceedingly wealthy. When David was fleeing Absalom at his most wretched, he brought beds, grain, and food to support the king and his followers. Later David invited him to the palace to enjoy life, but he humbly declined, asking only to return home to spend his last years in peace. An elder generous in distress and detached before glory.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Barzillai supplied generously in David's distress, yet was detached and content before glory. Make me generous in others' distress and content before fame, generous and not greedy. Amen.",
