  "lesson_en": "Taking advantage of his master's misfortune for private gain",
  "summary_en": "A servant of Saul's house, serving Mephibosheth.",
  "witness_en": "Ziba was a servant of Saul's house, assigned to serve Mephibosheth. When David fled Absalom, he came with provisions, but took the chance to slander, saying his master Mephibosheth hoped to restore the kingdom, and cheated him of his estate. Slandering for private gain in his master's misfortune is a servant's unfaithfulness.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Ziba slandered for private gain in his master's misfortune. Remove from me the heart that profits from chances and harms with slander, making me hold true loyalty toward those I serve. Amen.",
