  "applications": [
   "遇到亵渎与恐吓的言语，带到神面前祷告",
   "不被狂言动摇对神的信心",
   "谨守自己的口，不亵慢神圣的事"
  ],
  "scriptures": [
   "王下18-19"
  ],
  "prayer": "主啊，拉伯沙基狂言羞辱祢，祢一夜之间堵住了他。求祢坚固我的信心，不被恐吓动摇，并谨守我的口尊祢为圣。阿们。",
  "lesson_en": "Arrogant words shaming God are finally stopped by God",
  "summary_en": "An Assyrian commander who shamed God before the walls of Jerusalem.",
  "witness_en": "The Rabshakeh was the Assyrian king's commander who, before the walls of Jerusalem, taunted loudly in the Judean dialect, shaming and blaspheming the LORD to shake the people's hearts. Hezekiah spread his words before God in prayer, and that night God struck the Assyrian army, stopping all the arrogant words.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, the Rabshakeh shamed You with arrogant words, and in one night You stopped him. Strengthen my faith, unshaken by threats, and guard my mouth to honor You as holy. Amen.",
