  "witness_en": "Shear-jashub was Isaiah's son, his name meaning 'a remnant shall return.' God told Isaiah to take him to meet King Ahaz, and the child's name was itself a message to the terrified king: after judgment, God will surely keep a returning remnant. His small presence carried God's hope.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Shear-jashub's name declares a remnant shall return. Make me hold Your hope of keeping a remnant amid judgment and terror, that my life too be a sign conveying hope. Amen.",
  "follow_en": [
   "Carrying God's message of hope by his very existence"
  ],
  "caution_en": [],
  "applications_en": [
   "Trust that in judgment God always keeps the hope of 'a returning remnant'",
   "Let your life too be a sign conveying hope",
   "Hold the promise that the remnant will survive in turbulent times"
  ]
