  "witness_en": "Jezreel was the firstborn of the prophet Hosea, the name commanded by God as a sign of judgment on the house of Jehu for shedding blood and on the north. Yet 'Jezreel' originally means 'God sows'—in the name of judgment, God also planted the hope of replanting and revival.",
