  "lesson_en": "The wife who offered a vicious scheme also sensed the downfall",
  "summary_en": "Haman's wife, who advised building a gallows to harm Mordecai.",
  "witness_en": "Zeresh was Haman's wife. When Haman raged against Mordecai, it was she and his friends who advised: build a gallows fifty cubits high and hang Mordecai on it. Yet when Haman began to decline, she changed her tune: you will surely fall before Mordecai. She both abetted evil and foresaw the downfall with the wind.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Zeresh gave Haman a vicious scheme. Make me a voice for good in my home, not abetting people in evil, nor bending with the wind for self-protection. Amen.",
  "follow_en": [],
