  "witness_en": "Zebedee was the father of James and John, a fisherman of Galilee. When Jesus called his two sons, they at once left their father and the boat and followed the Lord. Zebedee did not stop them—he willingly let go, letting his sons answer a higher call, while he kept his own trade.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Zebedee willingly let his two sons leave the boat to follow You. Make me too not hinder those I love from answering Your call, faithful in my own duty. Amen.",
