  "lesson_en": "Opposing the true word, sinking into darkness himself",
  "summary_en": "Also called Bar-Jesus, the magician struck blind for opposing Paul.",
  "witness_en": "Elymas (also Bar-Jesus) was a sorcerer and false prophet who strongly opposed Paul, trying to keep the proconsul from believing the true word. Paul, filled with the Spirit, fixed his eyes and rebuked him for 'deceit and villainy,' striking him temporarily blind. Whoever opposes the true word and hinders people from believing pushes himself into darkness.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Elymas opposed the true word and hindered people from believing, sinking into darkness himself. Make me never hinder people from turning to You, far from deceit, one who draws people near to You. Amen.",
