  "witness_en": "Eutychus was a young man; as Paul preached until midnight at Troas, he sank into deep sleep on the windowsill, fell from the third floor, and was picked up dead. Paul went down and fell on him, and he came to life, and the people were greatly comforted. Weak and embarrassed as he was, the Lord's grace still came to him.",
