  "prayer": "主啊，亚拿尼亚为美名欺哄圣灵而亡。求祢使我在祢面前全然诚实，奉献事奉不慕虚名，不向祢做表面功夫。阿们。",
  "lesson_en": "Lying to the Holy Spirit for a good name",
  "summary_en": "Who with his wife Sapphira conspired to deceive the Holy Spirit and died.",
  "witness_en": "Ananias and his wife Sapphira sold a field and secretly kept back part, yet claimed to have given it all. The problem was not keeping money (which was free), but 'lying to the Holy Spirit,' lying for a good name. Peter exposed it in a word, and he fell dead on the spot. Falsehood before God is far more terrible than poverty.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Ananias died lying to the Holy Spirit for a good name. Make me wholly honest before You, giving and serving without chasing vanity, doing no surface work toward You. Amen.",
