  "witness_en": "The Nicolaitans were a heretical group in the early church, mentioned twice by the Lord in His letters to Ephesus and Pergamum—the Ephesian church 'hated their works,' which accorded with the Lord's heart; Pergamum, however, tolerated them. They likely held that one could compromise with idolatry and immorality. The Lord plainly said: this is what I hate.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, the works of the Nicolaitans are what You hate. Make me discern and reject teaching that leads to compromise with the world, hating sin yet loving sinners, guarding the community's purity. Amen.",
