  "witness_en": "Susanna was one of the women who followed Jesus and supplied the Lord and the disciples from their own means, named by Luke with Mary Magdalene and Joanna. Their supply quietly held up the Lord's preaching team. Besides these named, there were 'many other women'—those who serve the Lord never lack such quiet givers.",
  "prayer_en": "Lord, Susanna supplied Your preaching work with her means. Make me too willingly supply Your ministry with resources, giving quietly behind the scenes, holding up Your work. Amen.",
